<TITLE>

The Moffett building controversy at UT


</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY bgcolor="ffffff">
<h3>

Information about the controversy surrounding the naming of the <!WA0><!WA0><a
href="http://www.utexas.edu/cons/admin/mbb/index.html">new molecular
biology building</a> at the University of Texas at Austin (UT) for Jim Bob
Moffett, chairman of <!WA1><!WA1><a href="http://www.fcx.com">Freeport-McMoRan
Copper and Gold</a>.



</h3>
<p>

<!WA2><!WA2><a href="http://www.motherjones.com/mother_jones/SO96/bryce.html">
Spinning Gold</a>, Robert Bryce, <em>Mother Jones</em>,
September-October, 1996.  "By keeping journalists away from its
Indonesian mine--which contains gold, silver, and copper valued at $50
billion--New Orleans-based Freeport-McMoRan has managed to put its
spin on environmental and human rights abuses near the mine." <!WA3><!WA3><a
href="http://www.mojones.com/mother_jones/ND96/backtalk_jump.html#spin">
Freeport replies</a>, <em>Mother Jones</em>, November-December, 1996.

<p>

<!WA4><!WA4><a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/boyer/fp/ng.html">Freeport's Grasberg mine</a>.  National Geographic
photo, at <!WA5><!WA5><a
href="http://www.moles.org/motherlode/freeport/freeport.html"> Project
Underground</a>.  Some <!WA6><!WA6><a
href= "http://www.moles.org/motherlode/freeport/photos.html">other
pictures</a> of Freeport's mine at <!WA7><!WA7><a
href="http://www.moles.org/"> Project
Underground</a>.

<P>

<br clear=all>

<!WA8><!WA8><img src ="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/boyer/fp/tailings.gif" alight=left> <br><br> Tailings from the
Grasburg mine pour into a tributary of the Ajkwa River, <em><!WA9><!WA9><a
href="http://www.hyperweb.com/txobserver">Texas Observer</a></em>, <!WA10><!WA10><a
href="http://www.hyperweb.com/txobserver/indonesia.htm">November 17,
1995</a>, p. 9.  <!WA11><!WA11><a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/boyer/fp/tailings.jpeg">43k jpeg version</a>.

<br clear=all>

<P>

<!WA12><!WA12><img
src="http://www-cgi.cnn.com/EARTH/9602/irian_jaya/river_flow_large_cap.jpg"
align=left> <br> <br> "Tribal leaders and environmentalists claim the
mine in the rugged mountains is the source of tons of toxic wastes
that are killing portions of a river and acres of rain forest. Many of
the tribes also complain that their land has been taken without
compensation by the Indonesian government, and that human rights
activists have been abused and some even murdered by the Indonesian
military." <!WA13><!WA13><a
href="http://www-cgi.cnn.com/EARTH/9602/irian_jaya/index.html">Gold
and blood in the wilderness</a>, <em>CNN</em> February 21, 1996.
<! This one seems to have disappeared.
 href="http://cnn.com/WORLD/9604/15/newsbriefs/index.html#1"
More blood
CNN April 14>

<br clear=all><P>

<p>

"Freeport's Grasberg mine in the remote and rugged province is
`arguably the most valuable single mineral discovery ever made,'
(Freeport vice-president) Murphy told Reuters in outlining current
exploration work."  Reuter, October 9, 1996.

<br>
<p>

"Probably everyone in Austin has something from the Freeport copper
mine in their house.  The mine is now producing about 8% of the
world's copper."  UT Geological Sciences Department chairman <!WA14><!WA14><a href="http://www.ig.utexas.edu/staff/cloos/cloos.html">Mark Cloos</a>, Oct. 6, 1996.

<br>
<p>

<h3> Contents </h3>
<ul>

<li><!WA15><!WA15><a href="http://www.fcx.com">Freeport Copper and Gold's web
page</a>.  A source of extensive information about Freeport, well
organized.  Especially relevant is this <!WA16><!WA16><a
href="http://www.fcx.com/fcx/ia.htm">subpage</a>, which contains
explicit responses to many of the allegations that have been made
against Freeport.  (Rumor has it that there is a new book out just
published by Freeport entitled <em>GRASBERG: Mining the Richest and
Most Remote Deposit of Copper and Gold in the World, in the mountains
of Irian Jaya, Indonesia</em>. 1-800-535-7094.)

<li> <!WA17><!WA17><a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/boyer/fp/sec1.html">Basic documents</a> about human-rights
violations and environmental damage near the Freeport mine in <!WA18><!WA18><a
href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/boyer/fp/irian-jaya.html">Irian Jaya</a>.

